---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
import NextStep from '../../components/NextStep.astro';

export const title = "Funding Your Maine Dispensary: A Founder's Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Funding Your Maine Dispensary | Startup Capital & Credit" 
  description="Expert guide to funding your Maine cannabis business. Learn about bootstrapping with $5k-$10k, using business lines of credit, and asset protection."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579621970563-ebec7560ff3e?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Funding Your Maine Dispensary</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Strategies for capital, credit, and asset protection</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="The Fuel for Your Passion" type="passion">
      Funding is the engine that turns your vision into a reality. Whether you're starting small with personal savings or building a professional credit line, understanding how to structure your finances is the first step toward long-term independence.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Starting Small: The $5,000 Bootstrap</h2>
      <p>Can you start a cannabis business with $5,000? In Maine, the answer is <strong>yes</strong>, but scale is key. While a full adult-use storefront has high entry costs, $5,000 is an excellent starting point for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Registered <a href="/glossary/#caregiver">Caregiver</a> Operations:</strong> Lower fees and simpler zoning.</li>
        <li><strong>Boutique Cultivation:</strong> Starting a small-scale Tier 1 canopy.</li>
        <li><strong>Ancillary Services:</strong> Consulting or delivery support (where permitted).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Starting small allows you to build "Sweat Equity" and a proven track record before seeking larger investment.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Using a Business Line of Credit</h2>
      <p>Many founders have personal savings (e.g., $10,000) but prefer to use a <strong>Business Line of Credit</strong> to protect themselves. This is a smart, professional move.</p>
      
      <h3>The Process for Cannabis Credit:</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Establish a Legal Entity:</strong> Form an LLC or Corporation to separate yourself from the business.</li>
        <li><strong>Open a Cannabis-Friendly Bank Account:</strong> Work with local Maine credit unions that specialize in the industry.</li>
        <li><strong>Build Business Credit:</strong> Apply for a line of credit using your business EIN. Be prepared to provide a solid <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-business-plan/">business plan</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Guarantee:</strong> Be aware that for a new business, banks may still require a personal guarantee, but the line of credit remains a business liability.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Asset Protection Tip" type="tip">
      Always keep your business and personal finances 100% separate. Use different accounts, cards, and tax filings. This "Corporate Veil" is your best defense for protecting your personal home and savings.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Maine Banking Partners</h2>
      <p>Because cannabis is federally illegal, traditional big banks won't help. Look toward:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Local Maine Credit Unions</li>
        <li>Specialized Cannabis Lending Firms</li>
        <li>Private Equity/Angel Investors in the Maine market</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">Dispensary Startup Cost Breakdown</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute financial or legal advice. Consult with a qualified Maine cannabis CPA or attorney.</em></p>
    </section>

    <NextStep currentPath="/guides/maine-cannabis-funding-guide/" />
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  ul, ol { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
